Implementation Plan - Smart WiFi Intruder Detector
Goal Description
Create a Python-based Smart WiFi Intruder Detector that scans the local network, identifies connected devices, manages a list of known devices, and alerts the user when a new (unknown) device connects.

User Review Required
NOTE

This tool requires administrative privileges (root/admin) to perform network scanning using Scapy.

Proposed Changes
Core Logic
[NEW] 
network_scanner.py
Uses scapy to send ARP requests.
Returns a list of active devices (IP, MAC).
[NEW] 
device_manager.py
Manages known devices (storage in JSON/CSV).
Identifies device vendors using MAC addresses.
Checks for new devices.
[NEW] 
alert_system.py
Handles notifications (console, system sound, or potential email/webhook integration).
User Interface
[NEW] 
ui_manager.py
Uses rich library for a beautiful terminal UI.
Displays active scan results and alerts.
Entry Point
[NEW] 
main.py
orchestrates the components.
Verification Plan
Manual Verification
Run python main.py (as admin).
Verify that known devices are listed.
Verify that a new device (e.g., phone toggling WiFi) triggers an alert.